  "prompt": "What's the Chabad view on lesbians?",
  "response": "Chabad, as part of Orthodox Judaism, maintains traditional views on sexuality that align with classical Jewish texts and teachings. In general, Orthodox Judaism does not endorse same-sex relationships or marriages and views them as inconsistent with Jewish law (Halacha). \n\nHowever, Chabad emphasizes the importance of treating all individuals with kindness and respect, recognizing their inherent dignity. The community is encouraged to express compassion and understanding towards everyone, including those who identify as part of the LGBTQ+ community. Chabad's approach may vary on an individual basis, and some members may be more open and accepting than others.\n\nFor a deeper understanding of specific viewpoints or teachings, it may be beneficial to consult Chabad literature or engage in discussions with knowledgeable members of the community.",
